[[Image:Laxdaela Saga - Map - Project Gutenberg eText 17803.jpg|thumb|300px|Map of the district of the ''Laxdæla saga'', from an English language translation]]
'''Laxárdalur''' ([[Old Norse]]: ''Laxárdalr'') is a region in northwestern [[Iceland]]. It was the setting for the ''[[Laxdæla saga]]'' and the home of such famous early Icelanders as [[Aud the Deep-Minded (Ketilsdóttir)|Aud the Deep-Minded]], [[Hoskuld Dala-Kollsson]], [[Hrútr Herjólfsson]], and [[Olaf the Peacock]].

