{{Update|reason=https://www.amazon.com/Oswald-Lucky-Rabbit-Cartoons-Editions/dp/148478037X|date=August 2017}} The following is a complete '''list of cartoons''' starring '''[[Oswald the Lucky Rabbit]]'''.
[[Walt Disney]] produced 27 cartoons during 1927–1928, 25 cartoons were produced after Walt Disney's departure during the Winkler years (1928–1929), and 142 cartoons were produced by [[Walter Lantz]] during 1929–1943, making 194 cartoons in total.
==Theatrical shorts==
===The Disney years===
====1927==== {| class="wikitable" |- !Film !Notes |- |''[[Poor Papa]]'' |First cartoon produced in series (in 1927), initially rejected but released a year later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneyshorts.org/years/1928/poorpapa.html|title=''Poor Papa'' at The Encyclopedia of Disney Animated Shorts|accessdate=2010-12-12|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101127012131/http://www.disneyshorts.org/years/1928/poorpapa.html|archivedate=2010-11-27|df=}}</ref> Animated by [[Ub Iwerks]] and the entire Disney Oswald staff. Disney was unable to access a print of ''Poor Papa'' in time for the 2007 DVD,<ref>http://ramapithblog.blogspot.it/2010/09/lucky-new-oswald-finds.html</ref> but today owns a 16mm print of the short, and released it on the "Signature Edition" Blu-Ray of ''[[Pinocchio (1940 film)|Pinocchio]]'' in 2017. |- |''[[Trolley Troubles]]'' |Animated by [[Ub Iwerks]] and the entire Disney Oswald staff. The cartoon was reissued in 1931 by [[Walter Lantz]] with music and sound effects. |- |''[[Oh Teacher (film)|Oh Teacher]]'' |Cartoon reissued by Walter Lantz. A few sequences went missing and others were reordered when the cartoon was reissued. Animated by [[Ub Iwerks]] and the entire Disney Oswald staff. |- |''[[The Mechanical Cow]]'' |Cartoon reissued by Walter Lantz. Animated by [[Ub Iwerks]] and the entire Disney Oswald staff. |- |''[[Great Guns!]]'' |Cartoon reissued by Walter Lantz. Animated by [[Ub Iwerks]] and the entire Disney Oswald staff. |- |''All Wet'' |Cartoon reissued by Walter Lantz. Directed by [[Ub Iwerks]]. Animated by Iwerks and the entire Disney Oswald staff. |- |''The Ocean Hop'' |A few sequences went missing when the cartoon was reissued. Animated by [[Hugh Harman]] and [[Rollin Hamilton]]. The last Disney Oswald cartoon that was reissued by Walter Lantz. [https://drive.google.com/open?id=1Tc3Ikxppi165nZ3uQzRToA7qre1v7fIK ''The Ocean Hop'' at Google Drive] |- |''The Banker's Daughter'' |Lost cartoon. One story sketch page and a sketch of the title card survive.<ref>http://www.animationscoop.com/oswald-the-lucky-rabbit-celebrated-in-definitive-new-book-to-mark-90th-anniversary/</ref> Animated by [[Ub Iwerks]] and [[Friz Freleng]]. |- |''[[Empty Socks]]'' |A version has been found in 2014 with 30 to 60 seconds missing.<ref>https://ap.mnocdn.no/images/847dd8ec-0694-40d1-8cc7-9583714a4a8b?fit=crop&q=80&w=780</ref> <ref>http://www.jbkaufman.com/sites/default/files/Empty%20Socks.jpg</ref> <ref>https://images.thestar.com/content/dam/thestar/entertainment/movies/2014/12/12/disneys_longlost_first_christmas_film_turns_up_near_the_arctic_circle/empty_socks.jpg</ref> Animated by [[Hugh Harman]] and [[Rollin Hamilton]]. |- |''Rickety Gin'' |Lost cartoon. Animated by [[Ub Iwerks]] and [[Friz Freleng]]. |}
