s almost complete, though a few sequences are still missing. Animated by [[Ub Iwerks]], [[Hugh Harman]], [[Rollin Hamilton]], [[Ben Clopton]], and [[Les Clark]]. |- |''[[Hungry Hoboes]]'' |Available with the latest release of ''[[Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs (1937 film)|Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs]]'' in 2016. A once missing cartoon, it was rediscovered in a vault in England in November 2011. |- |''[[Oh, What a Knight]]'' |Remade as a Mickey Mouse 1933 short ''[[Ye Olden Days]]''. |- |''Sky Scrappers'' |Remade as a Mickey Mouse 1933 short, ''[[Building a Building]]''. |- |''[[The Fox Chase]]'' |Animated by [[Hugh Harman]] and [[Rollin Hamilton]] |- |''[[Tall Timber (1928 film)|Tall Timber]]'' |Animated by [[Hugh Harman]] and [[Rollin Hamilton]] |- |''[[Sleigh Bells (film)|Sleigh Bells]]'' | Rediscovered in 2015. Directed by [[Walt Disney]] and [[Ub Iwerks]].<ref name="SleighBells">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-34711495 |title='Lost' Disney cartoon Sleigh Bells to be screened |accessdate=November 3, 2015 |work=BBC News}}</ref> |- |''Hot Dog'' |Lost cartoon, but a storyboard page of the cartoon survives.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://baxterfilms.tumblr.com/post/21893169854/storyboard-pages-for-the-last-of-the-disney|title=Baxterfilms : Storyboard pages for the last of the Disney...|publisher=}}</ref> |- |''High Up'' |Re-discovered by [[David Gerstein]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BaZgURKhg3Y/|title=Dave Bossert on Instagram: Here is a frame from the climax of HIGH UP. It is the 27th Walt Disney Oswald short that was rediscovered by my friend David Gerstein. There is more information on it in my Oswald book. BTW, if you’ve got a copy of the Oswald book and like, please consider doing a quick review on Amazon.|publisher=}}</ref>. Erroneously thought to be a Winkler short before rediscovery proved otherwise.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fanboynation.com/disney-rarities-reveals-lost-oswald-lucky-rabbit-cartoon/|title=Disney Rarities Reveals the Lost Oswald the Lucky Rabbit Cartoon!|publisher=}}</ref> Last Disney Oswald cartoon. Directed by [[Hugh Harman]] and [[Rollin Hamilton]]. |}
