====1943==== {| class="wikitable" |- !Film !Notes |- |''[[The Egg Cracker Suite]]'' |This title is a play on ''The Nutcracker Suite'', composed by Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky. Though Oswald's screen career concludes in this cartoon, he would have a long run in comic books and a cameo in ''[[Well Oiled (film)|Well Oiled]]'' and ''[[The Woody Woodpecker Polka]]''. This was one of the few Oswald cartoons produced in color. Emery Hawkins' first onscreen credit at Walter Lantz Productions, and the only Lantz short directed by Ben Hardaway and Hawkins. |}
